{
  "stem": "8610.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they sent them back to Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I can understand they wanted to empty the camp because they wanted to make room for-- perhaps, for the invalids or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there was this question of repatriation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Our people, our Jews from Poland, said no.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So where do you want to go?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's only one country-- Palestine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whether they'd ever been Zionists is not the point.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there was no other country would have them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "England didn't take anybody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "America wouldn't have any more.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The gates were barred and bolted.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So where do they go?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "To sit there and rot?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So there was no way out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had to come back to England for a brief visit [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to report to the local Jewish community what was happening.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I held a meeting at the headquarters of the Rothschild house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I painted a picture of what I'd seen in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I looked around at these representatives of Anglo Jewry, and I thought to myself, they are looking as though I'm telling them something they've never heard about.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They hadn't heard of what was going on inside Germany?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't get much reaction.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I went to see Sir Herbert Emerson, who was the High Commissioner for Refugees.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He received me very nicely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I explained the situation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, I'm particularly concerned about the future of these people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Where are they going to go from here?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There's only one place.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They want to go to Palestine-- particularly younger element want to go  to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He looked very sad, raised his hands in horror and said, I'm terribly sorry.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I sympathize with you completely.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
